Police have arrested a man in Bureti for allegedly killing his son who refused to go to school. The 16-year-old Gilbert Kiprono was pronounced dead on arrival at Kapkatet Hospital. The father is accused of hitting him with a big stick. Area police boss Ali Abdullahi on Wednesday said they arrested the man who faces a murder charge. He told the Star on the phone the suspect used excessive force by hitting the boy on the head with a big stick. The body of the former pupil of Chesanga Primary School was taken to Kapkatet Hospital mortuary. Click here for the latest political news